# 4. 身近な人にも

Shiho: Okay. Aside from some tiny mistakes, I thought that was a good run.
Saki: Woohoo! We got Shiho's seal of approval!
Shiho: Don't get ahead of yourself... But this seems like a good place to stop. Why don't we take a break here before we go back and start making fixes?
Rin: Oh, in that case, can you tell us about the work research shadowing program you told us about the other day?!
Rin: How was it?! Did you have fun?!
Ichika: Yeah, and we learned a lot.
Luka: Oh, that's right. Ichika, Honami, you two went to visit a company that produces music videos and commercials, yes?
Honami: Yes, since we'll likely be shooting more videos in the future. We thought it'd be good for us to learn more about the production process.
Honami: On the day of our shadowing, we got to edit an actual music video. I was astonished by how glamorous it looked in the end.
Ichika: I know we've already shot a couple ourselves, but it was fun to learn about the tricks professionals use to give videos an impactful punch.
MEIKO: I see. It sounds like you two had a wonderful experience.
Len: How about you two, Saki, Shiho? Which company did you visit?
Saki: We visited a company that plans and operates all sorts of events!
Saki: Not only did we get to see how they run things, we even got to plan our own event!
Rin: Wait, that sounds super fun! What kind of event did you guys get to plan?
Shiho: We can't talk much about it since it was based on a real business deal, but it was a product promotion event for a famous stationery company.
Shiho: Our event involved having the guests make message cards for White Day.
Miku: Oh, message cards?
Saki: Hehe. We thought it'd be the perfect way for people to thank those they care about most during White Day!
Shiho: Not only does it help promote their products, it also follows their mission statement of helping people send their thoughts to others.
Saki: It gets even better. The company just happened to be planning a really similar event...
Saki: And we get to help them run things as part-timers!
Ichika: Wow, really? You're getting actual work experience? That's pretty incredible.
Honami: I know you'll do a great job.
Saki: Thanks! We'll do our very best!
Rin: Telling others how you feel through message cards, huh...?
Rin: That's such a great idea! What if we also tried doing that, you guys?!
KAITO: We? As in us?
Rin: Well, obviously! I feel like writing some now, because there's just so much I wanna tell all of you♪
MEIKO: Haha. You're so pure, Rin!
Rin: Hey, don't treat me like a little kid!
Rin: I'm not the only one who's gonna make cards. You and everyone else are too, MEIKO!
MEIKO: I know. I promise to write you a nice message, Rin.
Miku: You're right, it might be fun to make them together. Some things are hard to say outside of these sorts of opportunities.
Len: Like what?
Miku: Hmm... Like how we might start taking each other for granted since we're together all the time.
Miku: For example, MEIKO always does a good job of keeping us focused during practices, and Luka's subtly but constantly looking out for us...
Luka: Oh, Miku, does that mean you'd like me to pat your head as well?
Miku: That's not what I meant.
Len: I see. This does seem like a good opportunity to show just how much we appreciate each other.
KAITO: And writing a message would be easier than telling someone else directly...
Rin: Hehe. Then, let's give it a try!
Saki: (Thanking others for the things they do... The things you've taken for granted. Wouldn't that kind of event just be amazing?)
Saki: (I know it's a product promotion event, but I wanna do everything I can to help the guests show their appreciation for those they care about the most...!)
Rin: Oh, I know! Can I tag along when you two go help out with that event, Sakki?! I wanna see what it's like!
Saki: Sure! We can check it out together!
Shiho: Just make sure you don't get seen by the guests or staff, okay?
Rin: No problem!
Emu: Snippy, snippy, paste, paste... Sparkly and glittery☆
Luka: Oh, Emu, you seem to be in a good mood today.
Tsukasa: Yes, you still appear to have plenty of energy despite us just finishing practice.
Emu: Hehe. I'm really excited because we get to help out with that event soon!
Rui: Ah, this would be the White Day event you mentioned a while back.
Emu: Yup! It's gonna be all about showing appreciation for those you care about the most by writing message cards to them!
Emu: We're going to have the guests choose the card they like the most, and decorate them using masking tape and stickers...
Emu: We're even gonna have lots of other decorations available. That means they'll get to create one-of-a-kind cards♪
MEIKO: That sounds fun! I'd love to see how they turn out.
Emu: Hmm... The one I made for practice should be in my pocket... Oh, here it is!
Rui: Ah, what a fun-looking card.
Emu: Hehe☆ I used a ton of masking tape to make this one!
Tsukasa: What?! A bouquet pops up when you open it?!
KAITO: You can make pop-up cards?
Emu: Yup! You can even decorate the flowers using stickers and stamps!
Nene: Yeah, making these could be kinda fun...
MEIKO: What a fun and exciting way to show your appreciation for others!
Luka: Hehe. It really is♪ I'd probably sleep like a baby if I set this next to my pillow...
Emu: Oh, a fluffy card that feels like a pillow could also be really good!
